\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Our inheritance has been turned over to aliens, And our houses to foreigners. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 We have become orphans and waifs, Our mothers are like widows.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 We pay for the water we drink, And our wood comes at a price.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 They pursue at our heels; We labor and have no rest. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 We have given our hand to the Egyptians And the Assyrians, to be satisfied with bread. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Our fathers sinned and are no more, But we bear their iniquities.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Servants rule over us; There is none to deliver us from their hand.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 We get our bread at the risk of our lives, Because of the sword in the wilderness. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Our skin is hot as an oven, Because of the fever of famine.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 They ravished the women in Zion, The maidens in the cities of Judah.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Princes were hung up by their hands, And elders were not respected.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Young men ground at the millstones; Boys staggered under loads of wood. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 The elders have ceased gathering at the gate, And the young men from their music. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 The joy of our heart has ceased; Our dance has turned into mourning.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 The crown has fallen from our head. Woe to us, for we have sinned!\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Because of this our heart is faint; Because of these things our eyes grow dim; 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Because of Mount Zion which is desolate, With foxes walking about on it. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 You, O LORD, remain forever; Your throne from generation to generation.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Why do You forget us forever, And forsake us for so long a time?\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Turn us back to You, O LORD, and we will be restored; Renew our days as of old, 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Unless You have utterly rejected us, And are very angry with us! 
